com.github.yeetmanlord.bedwars_zeta.api.api_event_hooks.game

Class TrapTriggerEvent

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.bukkit.event.Event
      • com.github.yeetmanlord.bedwars_zeta.api.api_event_hooks.game.GameEvent
        • com.github.yeetmanlord.bedwars_zeta.api.api_event_hooks.game.TrapTriggerEvent
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    org.bukkit.event.Cancellable

    public class TrapTriggerEvent
extends GameEvent
implements org.bukkit.event.Cancellable
    Use this event to process code every time a trap is triggered
    This is used to modify the duration of the effects as well as the amplifier. This can also be used to run code once a trap is triggered allowing for custom traps. Canceling this events prevents this trap from triggering. entirely
    Author:
    YeetManLord
    API Note:
    If you cancel this event DO NOT RUN ANY CODE because it will continue to run over and over because this trap is still registered with the team. Only cancel when you want nothing else to happen. If you want to run code when the trap triggers but override giving effects (say you want to teleport all players on the defending team back to base) then use setPreventEffects(boolean)
